---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---
<Layout title="CarCue — Support" description="CarCue support and help.">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-5 py-16">
    <a href="/" class="text-white/30 hover:text-white text-sm transition mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-1">
      ← Back to Home
    </a>
    
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-6 mb-2">Support — CarCue</h1>
    <p class="text-white/30 mb-10">We're here to help keep your car running smooth.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">For questions, bug reports, or feature requests, email us at:</p>
    <p class="text-white mb-6"><a href="mailto:bunjistudios@gmail.com" class="text-amber-400 hover:text-amber-300 underline text-lg">bunjistudios@gmail.com</a></p>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">We typically respond within 24 hours.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-4">FAQ</h2>
    
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">How does the AI Mechanic work?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">The AI Mechanic reads your vehicle's year, make, model, engine, mileage, and service history to give personalized advice. Ask it anything about maintenance, diagnostics, repair steps, or cost estimates. It's like having a knowledgeable mechanic friend who knows your car.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">What is the Vehicle Health Score?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Your Health Score (0-100) factors in overdue maintenance, service history frequency, vehicle age, mileage, and expired documents. Tap the ℹ️ button on the health ring to see exactly what's affecting your score and how to improve it.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">How does MPG tracking work?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Log at least two full-tank fill-ups with different odometer readings. CarCue calculates MPG from the miles driven between fill-ups divided by gallons pumped. The smart odometer picker auto-estimates your current mileage based on driving patterns.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">Will I lose my data if I switch phones?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">No! CarCue uses iCloud sync — your vehicles, service records, fuel entries, documents, and reminders all sync automatically across your Apple devices. New phone? Just sign in with the same Apple ID.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">How do I cancel my subscription?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Open iPhone Settings → tap your name → Subscriptions → CarCue Premium → Cancel. You'll keep Premium access until the end of your billing period.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">What's included in Premium?</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-white/60 mb-6 space-y-2 leading-relaxed">
      <li>AI Mechanic — personalized diagnostics, repair walkthroughs, cost estimates</li>
      <li>Vehicle Intel — market value, recall checks</li>
      <li>Document Vault — store insurance, registration, warranty docs with expiration alerts</li>
      <li>Receipt Scanner — AI-powered OCR extracts service details from photos</li>
      <li>Export Reports — professional PDF health reports and CSV service histories</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">What's free?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Unlimited vehicles, service tracking, fuel logging, maintenance reminders, Vehicle Health Score, and the nearby shop finder are all free forever.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white/90 mt-6 mb-3">Is the AI Mechanic a real mechanic?</h3>
    <p class="text-white/60 mb-6 leading-relaxed">No — the AI Mechanic is an AI assistant that provides informational guidance based on your vehicle's data. It's great for understanding issues, getting repair steps, and checking if costs are fair. For safety-critical repairs (brakes, airbags, steering), always consult a certified mechanic.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
